{'decision': 'Reject', 'title': 'ICLR 2018 Conference Acceptance Decision', 'comment': "This paper presents a sensible, but somewhat incremental, generalization of neural architecture search.  However, the experiments are only done in a single artificial setting (albeit composed of real, large-scale subtasks).  It's also not clear that such an expensive meta-learning based approach is even necessary, compared to more traditional approaches.

If this paper was less about proposing a single new extension, and more about putting that extension in a larger context, (either conceptually or experimentally), it would be above the bar.
"}
